<br>
Reloaded is also phenomenal, with the burly brawl and fights but it does seem to be to heavily dependent on the CG, for example some scenes when neo is flying in my opinion would have been better as bullet time sequences. But personally I loved all the fight scenes and the overall fighting styles.<br>
<br>
When I was watching the movie for the first time, I was thinking to myself...'Its wow! but the first was better'...but its the arkitecht that changed that opinion. Also it doesn't really do justice to rate reloaded just yet, because reloaded and revolutions are actually one big movie, in fact all three are. So once revolutions comes out, I'll be making my final decision. <br>
<br>
btw, what did you all understand by the arkitecht scene and neo stopping the sentinals?<br>
<br>
11MonkeyPunch, and any one else whose interested, the hidden access panels on the matrix site are zionmainframe access panels, there are three and so far there's only access to the third and second panels. The third panel is an 8 bit binary access and was the only one I knew about before reloaded, once reloaded came out they posted a code which gave access to panel 2. Panel 3 giave audio's and interviews and other such info during the time when reloaded was in production, oooits easy to hack because there's a small number of combinations. <br>
<br>
However panel 2 is a hexadecimal with over 4 billion possible combinations. Don't even think about hacking that one. The codes for the hex are given on the site itself in the news section, however they're usually hidden, try highlighting messages and you might just find a code. They also give clues so try and crack their meanings.<br>
<br>
Right, to get to panel 3, enter the high bandwidth site, on the menu, on the far right, you'll see a panel with a yellow bulb: the options panel. Click on it and you get a small tray come out, to the right of the low bandwidth button you'll see a square box, when you roll over it the navigator screen thing will not tell you what it is, click on it and it will open to show a green button that the navigator will show as binary access. Click on it and let the panel load, it will drop down just slide it open and flip the switches until the little green light goes on then click enter. Once you want to move on to the second panel, enter this code: 01101111<br>
<br>
In access panel two you'll get instructions on how to it. Search around the site before hand to look for some codes. Check out 0xA3B1A428, you'll need a fast connection and computer for that one.<br>
<br>
Anyway, enjoy.<br>
<br>
