I think me and my friend figured out why Neo is wearing that crazy blindfold. Look closely when he blows up that whole fleet of sentinals. Look right above the cloth over his eyes. It's all scratchy and bloody.<br>
<br>
Methinks Neo has no eyes... Also, I dont know if this has any bearing on this situation, but the Merovingian says to bring him the Oracle's eyes. Is it just me or are people losing eyes left and right.<br>
<br>
Also my own theory is that he loses them when he's fighting real life Smith. The one who he is right next to in the final moments of Reloaded. The part where real Smith is covered with blood and say, &quot;Look past the flesh and see your enemy...&quot; I think they just cleverly edited it so that no one caught on Neo has no freakin eyes. Again I could be wrong.<br>
<br>
Second notice right before the trailer ends they show some nifty Matrix coded scenes from the movie. If you look VERY closely it's the Oracles kitchen!! And there are three men around her (she's assumed to be the shiny glowy one, like Seraph). My guesses to the three men? Smith, Neo, and Merovingian. <br>
<br>
Finally if you slow down the trailer to look who the mystery guy who jumps in front of the subway car is, it's the bum from the subway who you more predominantly see in the video game Enter the Matrix. He was the one in the game who said, &quot; 23 days is how long Zion lasted last time. 23 days....&quot; Or something along those lines. I think that this bum is actually the original One. Or perhaps something of a memory or after image.... <br>
<br>
Again all of these theories are subject to change, but a lot of it seems to make sense. I think....<br>
